47
00:02:35,084 --> 00:02:37,247
Now, let's talk about Interview Tips.

48
00:02:37,247 --> 00:02:38,112
Do's.

49
00:02:38,112 --> 00:02:40,516
Think out loud - Explain your reasoning.

50
00:02:40,516 --> 00:02:43,329
Start simple - Then add complexity.

51
00:02:43,329 --> 00:02:46,093
Ask questions - Clarify requirements.

52
00:02:46,093 --> 00:02:49,254
Draw diagrams - Visual communication.

53
00:02:49,254 --> 00:02:52,259
Consider trade-offs - No perfect solution.

54
00:02:52,259 --> 00:02:54,591
Discuss alternatives - Show breadth.

55
00:02:54,591 --> 00:02:55,444
Don'ts.

56
00:02:55,444 --> 00:02:57,692
Don't dive into details too fast.

57
00:02:57,692 --> 00:02:59,783
Don't ignore scale requirements.

58
00:02:59,783 --> 00:03:01,862
Don't forget about failure cases.

59
00:03:01,862 --> 00:03:04,338
Don't be silent - Keep communicating.

60
00:03:04,338 --> 00:03:06,959
Don't be defensive - Accept feedback.

61
